cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MS, cs.CC, cs.NE

The paper describes the use of deep learning for predicting superconductivity based on chemical composition, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of computational methods for materials science (cs.MS) and the development of a predictive model (cs.CC). Finally, the paper involves the use of neural networks (cs.NE) for deep learning.
